{"ts":"2026-05-02T16:09:35.975Z","author":"audit-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/front_matter/id","value":"pm-9iho"},{"op":"add","path":"/front_matter/title","value":"PmCliError events leaking to Sentry via captureConsoleIntegration"},{"op":"add","path":"/front_matter/description","value":"All 8 current Sentry issues are PmCliError instances (user input errors). The beforeSend filter correctly returns null for PmCliError exception events, but the captureConsoleIntegration({ levels: ['warn', 'error'] }) may be re-capturing these as console-level events when they're printed to stderr. Should either (a) add PmCliError filtering to beforeSendTransaction as well, or (b) exclude PmCliError messages from captureConsole capture."},{"op":"add","path":"/front_matter/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/front_matter/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/front_matter/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/front_matter/tags","value":["audit","bug","sentry","telemetry"]},{"op":"add","path":"/front_matter/created_at","value":"2026-05-02T16:09:35.975Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/front_matter/updated_at","value":"2026-05-02T16:09:35.975Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/front_matter/author","value":"audit-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/front_matter/acceptance_criteria","value":"No PmCliError events appear in Sentry after fix"},{"op":"add","path":"/front_matter/parent","value":"pm-5zkg"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"4c526ad6bbbe62245a8325c7c167ed4959c75748ddf0c5e76a8696e507c5c704","message":"Document Sentry PmCliError leak"}
